instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The DT relies on a low‑level driver that periodically reads the two internal temperature sensors (sampling interval is not specified in the documents). Each reading is published to a RabbitMQ message broker running on the Raspberry Pi, which provides asynchronous, near‑real‑time synchronization between the physical twin and digital‑twin services. The controller subscribes to these messages, updates calibration algorithms and runs the simulation models. No explicit latency requirements or quantitative frequencies are given, so the temporal granularity of the overall DT is bound by the sensor polling rate and the message‑passing latency of the local RabbitMQ server."
