instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Incubator DT follows a centralized, component‑based architecture typical of CPS‑based digital twins. It comprises a low‑level driver for sensor acquisition, a communication server implemented with RabbitMQ that mediates messages between the driver and higher‑level components, and a controller that hosts two simulation models, calibration algorithms, monitors, and optimisation logic. Data flows from the physical sensors to the driver, then through RabbitMQ to the controller where models are updated and predictions generated. All components are deployed on the same Raspberry Pi, forming an integrated orchestration shown in Figure 6 of the report."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The DT lifecycle described in Document 1 consists of (i) a development phase where abstract models of the physical twin are constructed (e.g., CAD or dynamic differential‑equation models), (ii) an integration phase where sensor data collected from the PT are ingested and linked to the models, (iii) an operational phase in which calibration algorithms continuously update model parameters, (iv) a monitoring phase where algorithmic monitors evaluate safety and optimality, and (v) a decision‑execution phase where detected violations trigger human or automated actions on the PT. Transitions between phases are managed by the calibration and monitoring algorithms that feed back data to keep the cyber representation synchronised with the physical system."
]

